    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Boston</placeName>
                <date>May 3th 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Rev. Sir!</p>
            <p>Enclosed I forward to you some resolutions, which I am<lb/> ordered to get printed in
                your next Occident, &amp; for<lb/> the expenses you will please send in your
                bill.<lb/> You might be astonished for getting said resolutions<lb/> so late, but I
                have to inform you, that there is considerable<lb/> trouble since 6 months in these
                Congregation between the<lb/>
                <sic>germans</sic> &amp; Polanders for the last 11 years as you are<lb/> aware this
                Congregation has been carried on respectable<lb/> &amp; <sic>peacable</sic>, but
                last <date>Sept.</date> a good <sic>menni</sic> Polanders have been<lb/> admitted,
                &amp; troubles commenced. Already a compromise<lb/> has been effected, but when the
                good men of the legacy<lb/> of <persName>Judah Touro</persName> was known, the
                leaders of the polish<lb/> party, who care <sic>werri</sic> little about Judaism,
                still want the<lb/> management of the whole, could not be brought to a<lb/>
                <sic>peacable</sic> settlement, &amp; the matter is now pending before<lb/> courts
                of Laws. My <sic>objekt</sic> of mentioning to you is, as<lb/> your influence to
                some of the executors of <persName>Judah Touro</persName><lb/> to
                    <sic>reccomend</sic> some understanding &amp; to settle the trouble,<lb/> as
                both parties having organized under the same Charter,<lb/> &amp; each claiming the
                legacy &amp; the property &amp; <add>וכדי בזיון וקצף</add><lb/> Excuse me in
                troubling you about such matters.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am yours respectfully—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Moses Ehrlich</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
